---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SectionDivider from '../components/ui/SectionDivider.astro';
import headshot from '../assets/headshot.png';
import styles from './AboutPage.module.css';

const jsonLdPerson = JSON.stringify({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  '@id': 'https://billbergquist.dev/#person',
  name: 'Bill Bergquist',
  jobTitle: 'Web Developer',
  description: 'Web developer in Denver, CO with 14+ years of experience specializing in React, TypeScript, and modern web applications for small businesses.',
  url: 'https://billbergquist.dev',
  image: 'https://billbergquist.dev/og/about.png',
  address: {
    '@type': 'PostalAddress',
    addressLocality: 'Denver',
    addressRegion: 'CO',
    addressCountry: 'US',
  },
  sameAs: [
    'https://github.com/titomb345',
    'https://www.linkedin.com/in/bill-bergquist/',
  ],
  worksFor: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'Kasa',
  },
  alumniOf: {
    '@type': 'CollegeOrUniversity',
    name: 'Purdue University',
  },
  knowsAbout: [
    'React',
    'TypeScript',
    'Node.js',
    'Frontend Architecture',
    'Web Development',
    'Astro',
  ],
});
---

<Layout
  title="About Bill Bergquist — Denver Web Developer"
  description="14+ years of full-stack experience building websites for small businesses in Denver, Lakewood, and the Colorado Front Range. Custom code, local SEO, and enterprise-quality standards."
  canonical="/about"
  jsonLd={[jsonLdPerson]}
  ogImage="/og/about.png"
>
  <div class={styles.page}>
    <header class={styles.header}>
      <Image
        src={headshot}
        alt="Bill Bergquist — Denver Web Developer"
        width={160}
        height={160}
        class={styles.headshot}
      />
      <h1 class={styles.name}>Bill Bergquist</h1>
      <p class={styles.role}>Web Developer &middot; Denver, CO</p>
    </header>

    <main class={styles.content}>
      <section class={styles.intro}>
        <p class={styles.text}>
          I put 14+ years of professional engineering experience to work building websites for
          small businesses across Denver, Lakewood, and the Colorado Front Range. By day I'm a
          Staff Engineer at Kasa, leading frontend architecture and building internal tools that
          help teams ship faster. On the side, I help local businesses get online with sites that
          are fast, look great on every device, and actually show up in search results.
        </p>
        <p class={styles.text}>
          You get the same tools and standards I use in enterprise software, applied to your
          business site. No templates, no page builders. Just clean, custom code built by someone
          you can meet for coffee and talk to directly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <SectionDivider color="orange" />

      <section class={styles.approach}>
        <h2 class={styles.sectionTitle}>How I Work</h2>
        <p class={styles.text}>
          Every project starts with a conversation, not a sales pitch. I want to understand your
          business, who your customers are, and what you need the website to do. A restaurant
          needs online ordering and a menu that loads instantly on a phone. A contractor needs to
          show up when someone searches "plumber near me." The right solution depends on the problem.
        </p>
        <p class={styles.text}>
          I'm opinionated about code quality, but not precious about tools. React, Astro, vanilla
          JavaScript... the right choice depends on the project. I care about shipping things that
          work, load fast, and are maintainable by whoever comes next. If I build your site and you
          hire someone else to maintain it later, they should be able to pick it up without a manual.
        </p>
        <p class={styles.text}>
          I handle everything: design, development, SEO setup, hosting, and ongoing support. One
          person, one point of contact, no handoffs. Whether you need a new site from scratch or
          a redesign of something that isn't working, I'll give you an honest assessment of what
          it takes and what it costs.
        </p>
      </section>

      <SectionDivider color="orange" />

      <section class={styles.deliverables}>
        <h2 class={styles.sectionTitle}>What You Get</h2>
        <div class={styles.deliverableGrid}>
          <div class={styles.deliverableCard}>
            <span class={styles.deliverableIcon}>01</span>
            <h3 class={styles.deliverableTitle}>Custom Code</h3>
            <p class={styles.deliverableText}>
              No templates, no page builders. Every site is built from scratch with clean,
              hand-written code that loads fast and is easy to maintain.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class={styles.deliverableCard}>
            <span class={styles.deliverableIcon}>02</span>
            <h3 class={styles.deliverableTitle}>Local SEO</h3>
            <p class={styles.deliverableText}>
              Structured data, Google Business integration, and on-page optimization so your
              site actually shows up when people search for your business.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class={styles.deliverableCard}>
            <span class={styles.deliverableIcon}>03</span>
            <h3 class={styles.deliverableTitle}>One Point of Contact</h3>
            <p class={styles.deliverableText}>
              I handle design, development, hosting, and support. No agency layers, no
              handoffs. You talk to the person building your site.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class={styles.deliverableCard}>
            <span class={styles.deliverableIcon}>04</span>
            <h3 class={styles.deliverableTitle}>Enterprise Standards</h3>
            <p class={styles.deliverableText}>
              The same practices I use building software at scale: accessibility, performance
              budgets, responsive design tested on real devices.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <SectionDivider color="orange" />

      <section class={styles.background}>
        <h2 class={styles.sectionTitle}>Background</h2>
        <p class={styles.text}>
          I'm a Staff Software Engineer at Kasa, where I lead frontend architecture and build
          internal tooling. Before that, I spent over a decade at companies like Evite, GumGum,
          RevCascade, and PriceGrabber, working across the full stack. I've built everything
          from ad tech platforms and e-commerce systems to real-time collaboration tools and
          hospitality management software.
        </p>
        <p class={styles.text}>
          I studied Computer Engineering at Purdue University. Most of my career has been in
          frontend and full-stack development, with a focus on React, TypeScript, and Node.js.
          I also use AI tools like Claude Code to accelerate development, automate repetitive
          work, and explore solutions faster.
        </p>
        <p class={styles.text}>
          Building websites for local businesses started as a way to use the same skills I
          apply at work on something more personal. I like helping people get their business
          online without overpaying an agency or settling for a cookie-cutter template.
        </p>
        <div class={styles.credentialRow}>
          <div class={styles.credential}>
            <span class={styles.credentialValue}>14+</span>
            <span class={styles.credentialLabel}>Years Experience</span>
          </div>
          <div class={styles.credential}>
            <span class={styles.credentialValue}>Denver, CO</span>
            <span class={styles.credentialLabel}>Based Locally</span>
          </div>
          <div class={styles.credential}>
            <span class={styles.credentialValue}>Purdue</span>
            <span class={styles.credentialLabel}>BS Computer Engineering</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class={styles.servicesCta}>
        <p class={styles.servicesCtaText}>
          If you're a small business in Denver or the Colorado Front Range looking for a
          website, I'd love to help.
        </p>
        <a href="/services/" class={styles.servicesCtaLink}>View My Services &rarr;</a>
        <p class={styles.text} style="margin-top: var(--space-md); font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Or read about my work: <a href="/blog/rebuilding-critter-care-website/">Rebuilding the Critter Care Website</a> &middot;
          <a href="/blog/how-much-does-a-website-cost-denver/">How Much Does a Website Cost?</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
